<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-170] Document OFD (2.4 feature)</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-170</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Andreas has updated the glossary entry for obdfilter to define it as &quot;An older name for the OBD API data object operation device driver that sits between the OST and the OSD. In Lustre 2.4 this device has been renamed OFD.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;OFD needs to be defined in the glossary and referenced throughout the manual wherever obdfilter currently appears (many places).  Since this is a 2.4 change, it is out of scope for the Lustre Manual Quality Improvement project.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
